title: Bug 49235 - ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<? classSet is not expected class
description: Bug 49235 - ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<? The output is 'MySomeClass'.
OB: When using ServletContainerInitializer onStartup() method with a Set<Class<?>> classSet, the output shows 'MySomeClass'.
EB: The output should not show 'MySomeClass' as it is not expected.
SR:
1. Create a ServletContainerInitializer implementation. 
2. Implement the onStartup() method with a Set<Class<?>> parameter. 
3. Launch the application and verify the output. The output should not contain 'MySomeClass'.
